text: Earlville is a city in Illinois in the United States. It is in LaSalle County. == Notable people == * Steve Behel (1860-1945), MLB player for the Milwaukee Brewers and New York Metropolitans * Herbert O. Crisler, Head Football Coach and Athletic Director at University of Michigan, and namesake of Crisler Arena at the University * John J. Myers, Roman Catholic Archbishop of Newark, N.J * Gary K. Wolf, author of the novel Who Censored Roger Rabbit (1941-), which became the Movie Who Framed Roger Rabbit ==References== Category:Cities in Illinois
title: Earlville, Illinois
